cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SD 

The paper discusses a framework for feature extraction from diverse data types such as video, images, audio, and text. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), and software engineering (cs.SD). However, given that the paper focuses on feature extraction, which is a key component of computer vision and natural language processing workflows, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for feature extraction, which further supports the inclusion of cs.LG as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper's emphasis on developing an open-source framework for feature extraction suggests that it could also be relevant to the software engineering community, hence cs.SD as a possible sub-category.
